OL,5,F"Every single person in this room
OL,6,Ftoday involved in the memory stones,
OL,7,Fwe know what it's like, we understand
OL,8,Feach other, they are my new family."
OL,10,FPopular Warrenpoint woman Rosaleen
OL,11,FMoore's daughters had been dealing
OL,12,Fwith their grief on their own as a
OL,13,Ffamily.
OL,15,FJanine Curran and Donna Gribben said
OL,16,Fthey had been grappling with the guilt
OL,17,Fof working on the frontline of the
OL,18,Fhealth service just before their mum
OL,19,Ftook ill and died, aged 72.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/9
